Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!). Pick the @rosemary{1/2} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Pop the wedges on a low sided wide #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @olive oil{for roasting}, scatter over the rosemary then season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out and set aside, we will roast them later.

> Tip: Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Drain the @mozzarella{1}, tear into small pieces and pop into a #small bowl{}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}) and add to the mozzarella. Finely snip the @chives{1}(finely snipped) using #scissors{} into the bowl, season with salt and pepper and mix everything together. In another #bowl{} mix together half the @mayonnaise{2} with half the @dijon mustard{1/2}. Pop the @panko breadcrumbs{50} onto a #plate{}, add a drizzle of @olive oil{for coating}, season with salt and pepper and mix together.

Lay a @British chicken breasts{2} on your #board{} and place your hand on top to hold it in place. Insert a small #knife{} into the middle of the thickest part of the breast and make a slit about 5-6cm long. Cut about ¾ of the way into the fillet to create a pocket, not right through! Repeat with each chicken breast, then push the mozzarella mixture into the pocket with a #spoon{}. Close the opening with your hands to seal in the filling.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat!

Bake the wedges on the middle shelf of the oven until golden ~{30-35%minutes}. Turning halfway through cooking.

Meanwhile, smear one side of the chicken with a little of the remaining mayo to cover. Place it mayo-side-down into the crumbs. Smear the exposed side of the chicken with mayo and turn it over so both sides are coated. Repeat for the other fillet(s). Line a #baking paper{} with #baking paper{} and lay the chicken breasts onto it.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Bake the chicken on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. The cheesy filling will start to ooze out of the chicken but don't worry, it will become deliciously crispy!

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Pop the remaining mustard into a #medium bowl{} with the @balsamic vinegar{12} and @olive oil{for the dressing} and season with salt and pepper. Halve the @premium tomato mix{125} and pop them into the bowl with the @baby leaf mix{50} on top but don't mix together yet.

When everything is ready, mix the salad with its dressing using a #fork{}. Divide the cheesy chicken kievs between plates with the wedges, salad and the mustard mayo alongside to dip the wedges into. Enjoy!